http://druid.io/community/cla.html

@xvrl yeah, that is a problem. how about prepending every file name with "docs-" e.g.
XxX.md becomes docs-xxx.md ?
PS: I wish redirection was doable by creating one file and listing things there :(

@xvrl unfortunately it is not possible to have both "max" and "doubleMax" 
(similarly "min" and "doubleMin") supported.

I tried following, which did not work
'''
      //Note: max/min are same as doubleMax/doubleMin, but they are here to be backward compatible  
      //with druid-0.7.2 and before.  
      @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "max", value = MaxAggregatorFactory.class),  
      @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "min", value = MinAggregatorFactory.class),  
      @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "doubleMax", value = MaxAggregatorFactory.class),  
      @JsonSubTypes.Type(name = "doubleMin", value = MinAggregatorFactory.class),
'''

and it makes sense too. if this code worked then I wonder what json serializer would put into the "type" field on serialization of the object.

So, if we want to change "max" to "doubleMax" and "min" to "doubleMin" then we will have to make it a backward incompatible change.
We can probably afford to do it because we are just about to release 0.8.0 but not sure if everyone agrees.

@fjy actually I have no problems with all  of them being in one directory as bucketing can anyway be done in toc file, it isn't bad but to setup the redirection we need to either have different name or move all of them to some other folder[s].

One option is to have folder "docs/_content" and move all the newly created files there. we keep "docs/content" for files containing redirection links.
Or, do you want to bucket them in separate folders anyway?

Btw, on the min/max thing, I think it would make the most sense if the min/max aggregator were sensitive to the type of the data that it's operating on.

The interfaces currently don't allow for this, but I think if we add

```
ColumnThingie getColumn(String name)
```

To the ColumnSelectorFactory and then had 

```
interface ColumnThingie {
  toDimensionSelector(ExtractionFn fn);
  toFloatColumnSelector();
  toLongColumnSelector();
  toObjectColumnSelector();
  getType();
}
```

The aggregators could actually introspect and make a choice based on what type is there.  This could be done in a backwards compatible manner as well, where we deprecate the methods directly on the ColumnSelectorFactory and encourage things to go through this.

What do you think?  I can do a proposal email if people would prefer?

I had discussed with @xvrl briefly about what to do regarding the metadata update.

I'm in agreement with his point of view that only allowing the task to work as an indexing service task (and _NOT_ as a standalone hadoop job) would greatly simply things overall.

@cheddar : is there any objection to simply having this as ONLY an indexing task? (EDIT: indexing task which spawns a hadoop job, meaning it requires the indexing service to run on Hadoop)
